text.tspan: Pipelines are sets of tasks. A pipeline can
run anything the build machine is capable of.
Agent Pools are collections of agents that
can run the same pipelines (i.e. agent machines
have the correct capabilities such as Visual Studio
all the same, except that some
1. A pipeline is triggered manually, on a schedule, or when source code
2. Build agents are listening for requests
3. The pipeline searches its agent pool(s) for the next availabe agent that
can run all the steps. It queues the pipeline for an agent
4. The agent uses or creates a folder as its workspace, runs the pipeline
steps, and reports results to the CI server
